                            <comment id="12603354" author="milosz" created="Sun, 8 Jun 2008 09:00:24 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The JPA spec says:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;If there is no GROUP BY clause and the HAVING clause is used, the result is treated as a single group,&lt;br/&gt;
and the select list can only consist of aggregate functions. The use of HAVING in the absence of&lt;br/&gt;
GROUP BY is not required to be supported by an implementation of this speci&#64257;cation. Portable appli-&lt;br/&gt;
cations should not rely on HAVING without the use of GROUP BY.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If OpenJPA does not allow HAVING without GROUP BY, the paragraph in question could be changed to something like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;OpenJPA requires that if a query declares a HAVING clause, it must also declare a GROUP BY clause.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13008811" author="milosz" created="Sat, 19 Mar 2011 19:40:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OpenJPA supports HAVING without GROUP BY and assumes the database also allows such a construct. The manual is updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13198913" author="allee8285" created="Thu, 2 Feb 2012 16:23:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Close issue in preparation for 2.2.0 release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
